1.10	7_Squadron_SAAF	7 Squadron SAAF	7 Squadron was a unit of the South African Air Force which served in the Second World War as well as in South Africa between 1951 and 1992. During the war, the squadron was used as a fighter squadron deployed to the Western Desert as well as in the Aegean, Italy and Ceylon. The squadron was inactive from the end of the war until 1951 when it re-activated as a citizen force training squadron, a role it retained during two periods of active service until 1992, when it was disbanded for the last time.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bc/Supermarine_Spitfire_Mk_IX_-Indianapolis_Air_Show-24Aug2008.jpg/280px-Supermarine_Spitfire_Mk_IX_-Indianapolis_Air_Show-24Aug2008.jpg
